Name: Maida Vale Rd, High Wycombe
Description: There is a lot of traffic build-up on the exit from Roe Highway and little opportunity to turn right on Maida Vale Road. People then end up turning left and doing a quick turn at Plover Road/Maida Vale Road intersection because they can't cut through the traffic. It would very easily be solved by a roundabout to allow the traffic exiting Roe Highway to only have to give way to the right. Most traffic comes from the left. It is also difficult to see down Maida Vale Road to the right.

Name: Abernethy Rd & Grogan Rd, High Wycombe
Description: There is no feeder lane for vehicles turning right into Grogan Rd , constant rear end crashes here .  power pole needs moving to allow feeder lane to be made to allow us to safely turn into Grogan. And wait in que to turn .
Location: {"Sector": "", "PlaceName": "", "Territory": "", "Neighborhood": "High Wycombe", "CountryCode": "AUS", "District": "", "City": "Perth", "Region": "Western Australia", "Address": "Abernethy Rd & Grogan Rd", "AddNum": "", "ShortLabel": "Abernethy Rd & Grogan Rd", "Subregion": "Perth", "LongLabel": "Abernethy Rd & Grogan Rd, High Wycombe", "PostalExt": "", "Match_addr": "Abernethy Rd & Grogan Rd, High Wycombe, Western Australia, 6057", "Postal": "6057", "Type": "", "Addr_type": "StreetInt", "Block": "", "MetroArea": ""}
Comment 1: Steve: If you are on Grogan Rd trying to turn right into Abernethy Rd it can be very difficult and dangerous at times due to the high volume of traffic and the 70kph speed limit, and adding to it much of the traffic is very large road trains.  Also visibility is reduced as the barriers block the view of the oncoming traffic.
Comment 3: Steve: If heading South on Abernethy Rd and wanting to turn right into Grogan Rd, there is NO turning/off ramp to allow vehicles to safely queue while waiting to turn into Grogan Rd. Abernethy Rd is an extremely busy road with large amounts of heavy traffic including road trains. I use it daily a multitude of times and am staggered there hasn't been more accidents or even deaths there.
